      • fromObject

        public void fromObject(java.lang.Object obj)
                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Initialize IfxObject with the value in obj. It does the data conversion automatically from the obj type to IfxObject type. For example: In IfxInteger(), fromObject(Object obj) { if (obj instanceof Short) fromShort((Short) obj); }
        Parameters:
        obj - Convert the data value from obj to IfxObject
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
